<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
CLEAN AIR IS THEME OF POSTER CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Students in Ventura County public schools are participating in a national 
poster contest to celebrate the 20th anniversary of Earth Day. 
</P>
<P>
Sponsored locally by the Ventura County Air Pollution Control District, the 
theme of the contest is "Earth Day 1990: Care About Clean Air." 
</P>
<P>
Entries will be judged locally by the county school superintendent's office and 
a panel of judges, including Ventura County Supervisor Susan Lacey and Maureen 
Davidson, executive director of the Ventura Arts Council. 
</P>
<P>
Winning posters will be forwarded to Washington for the national competition. 
First-place winners will receive $500 each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
