<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
1 KILLED AFTER BEING THROWN FROM CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An unidentified man died Saturday when he lost control of his car on California 
1 south of Oxnard and was thrown out of the car, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The man, whose identity was not released pending notification of his relatives, 
was not wearing a seat belt, Claude Bell, a dispatcher for the California 
Highway Patrol, said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The man was driving south on California 1 about noon Saturday just south of 
Oxnard when he swerved off the road, hit some rocks and was thrown from the 
car, Bell said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
