HAYWARD; 
</P>
<P>
PRESIDENT NAMED AT CAL STATE CAMPUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Norma S. Rees, a higher education official in Massachusetts, was chosen to be 
the new president of Cal State Hayward. 
</P>
<P>
Rees will replace Ellis McCune, who is retiring after heading the 
12,825-student Northern California school for 23 years. Rees has been a vice 
chancellor for the Massachusetts Board of Regents of Higher Education since 
1987. There are two other women presidents in the 20-campus Cal State system, 
Gail Fullerton at San Jose and Jewel Plummer Cobb at Fullerton. 
</P>
