<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Red Hot Chili Pepper Band Members Arrested: Two members of the California rock 
band the Red Hot Chili Peppers were arrested Friday in Daytona Beach, Fla., on 
charges that they jumped from the stage during a spring-break performance and 
assaulted a woman in the audience. 
</P>
<P>
Bass guitarist Michael Balcary of Los Angeles, known by the stage name "Flea," 
was charged with battery, disorderly conduct and solicitation to commit an 
unnatural and lascivious act, authorities said. Drummer Chad Smith, 28, also of 
Los Angeles, was charged with battery. Authorities said the woman, who signed a 
complaint against the band members, was bruised and shaken. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
