<HEADLINE>
<P>
3.3 AFTERSHOCK RATTLES UPLAND; NO DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A small earthquake rattled the Upland area early Sunday morning, but there were 
no reports of damage or injury. 
</P>
<P>
The 3.3-magnitude temblor struck at 5:56 a.m., and was centered about 3 miles 
northwest of Upland, said Bob Finn, spokesman for Caltech in Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
Finn said Sunday's quake is the latest in a series of more than 500 aftershocks 
to a 5.5-magnitude temblor on Feb. 28. Finn said about 40 of the aftershocks 
have been strong enough to be felt by residents in Upland and surrounding San 
Gabriel Valley communities. 
</P>
<P>
A 3.5-magnitude aftershock struck the same area on March 8. 
</P>
<P>
Police and fire officials in Upland said they received numerous calls on 
Sunday's quake, but no reports of damage or injury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
