<P>
FIRE ON CRUISE SHIP OFF AUSTRALIA KILLS MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire in the engine room of a cruise ship off Australia killed one crew member 
and injured another Sunday, but the blaze was put out before it could reach the 
1,200 passengers or disable the vessel. 
</P>
<P>
P&amp;O Sitmar Cruises, owners of the Fairstar, said a 44-year-old boiler 
attendant died after suffering burns to 75% of his body during what was to be a 
routine testing of an auxiliary boiler. 
</P>
<P>
The ship was off the New South Wales state coast and heading back to Sydney 
after a 10-day cruise when the fire occurred. 
</P>
