<TEXT>
<P>
Three teen-agers were arrested early today in connection with the fatal 
shooting of a 31-year-old man during a fight just after midnight in the parking 
lot of an all-night convenience store in Garden Grove, police said today. 
</P>
<P>
David Eugene Davenport of Garden Grove was killed by a shotgun blast about 
12:10 a.m. outside a Circle K store at the intersection of Brookhurst Street 
and Katella Avenue, Garden Grove Police Sgt. Douglas Morrill said . 
</P>
<P>
Police said Davenport was visiting a clerk at the store and followed the three 
youths into the parking lot after he suspected that they had stolen some 
merchandise. Witnesses told police that after a confrontation, one of the 
assailants took a 20-gauge shotgun out of the car and fired it at Davenport, 
Morrill said. 
</P>
<P>
At about 12:30 a.m., a male and female juvenile were apprehended by Orange 
County sheriff's deputies at the Euclid Avenue entrance to the Garden Grove 
Freeway. They were in a car that matched the description of the one at the 
slaying scene, Morrill said. Cesar Maua Sustait, 19, of Santa Ana was arrested 
shortly afterward at his Santa Ana home on Euclid Avenue, Morrill said. Police 
also believe they have recovered the shotgun used in the murder. 
