<P>
SPORTS DAILY TO HIKE DISTRIBUTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The National said today that its circulation and ad sales are on target and 
that it will boost distribution by 40% soon by expanding in its first three 
markets: Los Angeles, Chicago and New York. 
</P>
<P>
Publisher Peter Price said March 15 that the sports daily is selling about 
200,000 of the 250,000 copies it prints every day, matching the target set for 
the paper. 
</P>
<P>
The National is distributed Sunday through Friday, and plans are to add six to 
12 more cities by Dec. 31, when Price hopes that half a million copies will be 
distributed every day. 
</P>
<P>
Advertisers have been told that it will start printing a second edition with a 
deadline three hours earlier than normal so papers can be distributed the next 
morning on newsstands farther away from the centers of its three markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
