PRODUCER IN HOSPITAL AFTER RIPTIDE RESCUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Famed X-rated entertainment producer Artie Mitchell remained hospitalized for 
hypothermia today after he and several family members were rescued from a 
dangerous riptide off Ocean Beach, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Mitchell, 44, was at the beach Sunday with three of his children, his brother 
Jim, and two of Jim's children when several of the youngsters got caught in the 
tide. 
</P>
<P>
"It was pretty ugly," said Mitchell, who was in fair and stable condition 
recovering from hypothermia at the University of California at San Francisco 
Medical Center. "I'm really happy to be alive. I almost kicked off in the 
emergency room . . . but it looks like I'm going to pull through it." 
</P>
<P>
The Mitchells operate Mitchell Bros. Film Group and are the city's most famous 
promoters of adult films and theaters. 
</P>
