<TEXT>
<P>
"Harry and the Hendersons," a new Fox series produced by Universal Television 
and Amblin Entertainment, has been given an unprecedented 72-episode 
commitment. 
</P>
<P>
The half-hour weekly sitcom, which will debut in January, is guaranteed a 
three-year run on the Fox network -- the longest commitment ever made to a 
syndicated or network show, according to the show's distributor, MCA. 
</P>
<P>
