<P>
HIRING HALL WILL BE TOWN MEETING TOPIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A town-hall meeting is planned for Thursday to discuss operations of a hiring 
hall for day laborers. The talk will cover who can use the hall and how it will 
benefit the community. 
</P>
<P>
English and Spanish brochures on the center will be available at the meeting, 
scheduled for 7 p.m. at El Modena Community Center, 18672 E. Center St. 
</P>
<P>
The hiring hall, or resource center as city officials are calling it, is 
scheduled to open Saturday and will be open from 6 a.m. to noon, Monday through 
Friday, and 7 a.m. to 11 a.m. on Saturdays. The trailer that will be used for 
the center is expected to arrive this week at the center's site at McPherson 
Road and Chapman Avenue, city spokeswoman Jane Owens said. 
</P>
<P>
Thirty days after the center opens, the Police Department will begin enforcing 
two ordinances that ban the solicitation of work on city streets. The ordinance 
carries maximum penalties of a $500 fine and a six-month jail sentence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
