<HEADLINE>
<P>
VICTIMS OF BLAZE REMAIN IN CRITICAL CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Seal Beach woman and her boyfriend who were burned in a fire at her duplex 
Saturday remained in critical condition Sunday as Orange County fire 
investigators continued to try to determine the cause of the blaze. 
</P>
<P>
Ralph Royston, 35, and Gay Kenyon, 24, suffered second- and third-degree burns 
after running through a wall of flames in attempting to escape a fire that 
broke out early Saturday morning in the living room of the duplex, fire 
investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
Both victims were airlifted to the burn unit at UCI Medical Center in Orange, 
where they remained in treatment Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Orange County fire officials investigating the blaze said Sunday that they had 
not yet discovered the cause. 
</P>
