<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Storytelling, a poetry reading and performance art will be presented March 31 
in a benefit for the needy at the Orange County Center for Contemporary Art in 
Santa Ana. The presentations, 30 minutes each, are free, but the center will be 
accepting blankets, men's heavy jackets, sweaters, shoes, sox, toothbrushes and 
other donations to give to Street People in Need (SPIN), a nonprofit 
organization helping the homeless. Storytelling, courtesy of Half Magic, a 
Tustin children's bookstore, begins at 11 a.m.; poetry by Laguna Beach writer 
Terry Kennedy at 1 p.m. and a performance art piece by Long Beach artist 
William Freeman at 2:30 p.m. Information: (714) 549-4989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
